<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880809-0148 </DOCNO><HL> Defense Contracts Awarded </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MD UIS ALD TXN </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Texas Instruments Inc.'s equipment group received a $27.9 million Army contract for TOW anti-tank missile sights.    Allied-Signal Inc.'s communications division received a $26.4 million Navy contract for Standard missile equipment.    Unisys Corp. got a $25.7 million Navy contract for Trident missile engineering services.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. was given a $12.2 million Air Force contract for aircraft weapons equipment. </TEXT></DOC>